10.	SUPPORT OF VERSIONS AND SERVICEABILITY
Without prejudice to Supplier’s obligation to strictly comply with the security requirements set forth in the Product Security Requirements Appendix, Supplier shall make the Software easy to maintain. Any new version, maintenance release, and patch shall be designed to be incorporated into a Customer's systems without disruption of system or software service operations. Wherever possible, versions, maintenance releases, and patches shall be suitable for remote installation, malfunction indications, failure analysis and operations. Standard interfaces shall allow remote configuration and data access.
If applicable and technically feasible, Supplier shall support and enable to deliver the customized Software to Zebracorp and its Customers. The customization (i.e. modifications to the Software that are not made generally available to Suppliers customers) of Software, or components thereof, shall include but not be limited to changes or adaptation of the relevant parts of the Software, e.g. to integrate Customer logo in the graphical user interfaces, to adapt java skins, to select languages etc and shall provide to Zebracorp any of existing customization tools and any associated Documentation and/or training. If a request for customization is not a documented feature of the Software, Zebracorp can request Supplier to develop the customization feature under a statement of work based on the fee structure as specified in Annex PPT, Service Price List.

input_sections.header: 11.	TOOLS, INTERFACES AND FORMS TO BE USED
input_sections.text:
11.	TOOLS, INTERFACES AND FORMS TO BE USED
Supplier shall use the tools, interfaces and forms as stipulated in this MSA.

12.	REVIEW MEETING
Regular review meetings shall be held between Zebracorp and Supplier to discuss the Services and any specific issues as they arise. If not otherwise agreed upon between the Parties, such meeting shall take place minimum once in a period of six months.

13. MANAGEMENT ESCALATION The purpose of the management escalation process identified in this Clause is to ensure that unresolved Errors are brought to the appropriate levels of Supplier‘s management for attention and action. This includes, but is not limited to Errors, which are not resolved in the applicable time frames as indicated in the respective Annex(es) and includes also Errors whose priorities cannot be agreed upon, Errors that turn into design change requests, undetermined Errors and sporadic Errors. The Management Escalation Process provides for and requires parallel escalation within both Zebracorp and Supplier to ensure that both Parties are informed about unresolved issues. The table below defines the timeframe for management escalation. For the purposes of the table below, “Management” means the manager of the functional area, regardless of actual title of his or her position. The contact names and phone numbers of the Supplier’s management are defined in the Annex POC. Any changes to such contact names shall be promptly communicated by Supplier to Zebracorp. 14.	COMPATIBILITY MATRIX FOR SOFTWARE
Supplier shall provide Zebracorp with a Compatibility Matrix as part of the release documentation for each version of Software.
